<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-30T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2367</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-31T00:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1916,
                                midnight</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>There is much uneasiness among the native population here and it is
                            reported that certain troops are ready to revolt. I am taking every
                            precaution but do not think that harm will befall foreigners as the
                            mutiny, if begun, will be innately a political demonstration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>